  / Education
  %aside{:style => 'background-image: url(/img/portfolio/education_header.jpg);'}
    %figcaption#education{:name => 'education'}
      %h2
        Education
        %a.portfolio-header-link{:href => '#education'} #
      %div
        %p I grew up wanting to become a teacher, and when I became a programmer, I achieved my dream.
  .container
    .row
      .col-lg-8.col-lg-offset-2.col-md-10.col-md-offset-1
        %ul#education_list.list-inline.text-center
          %li
            %h3 Blogging
            %img{:src => '/img/portfolio/blogging.jpg'}/
            %div
              %p I've been writing a developer-focused blog since 2011, now hosted here. At <a href='http://www.teehanlax.com/blog/author/ash/'>Teehan+Lax</a>, I began contributing to company blog as part of my job. I still do, now on <a href='http://artsy.github.io'>Artsy's developer blog</a>. I've also written posts for <a href='http://www.objc.io/contributors.html'>objc.io</a>.
              %p Blogging about has made me a better developer and a better writer.
          %li
            %h3 Treehouse Course
            %img{:src => '/img/portfolio/treehouse.jpg'}/
            %div
              %p In March, 2014, <a href='http://teamtreehouse.com'>Treehouse</a> invited me to Orlando to record a series of videos and screencasts to guide users through building a diary app for iOS. The app uses Core Data in order to persist data between application launches.
              %p I've also given real-world workshops all over, from Toronto to Milan.
          %li
            %h3 Speaking
            %img{:src => '/img/portfolio/speaking.jpg'}/
            %div
              %p I began speaking in the Toronto CocoaHeads group. After a while, I started submitting proposals to conferences, slowly building up experience. Not long after that, I started being invited to come speak at venues. I've spoken at local meetups in Warsaw and Copenhagen and at conferences from San Francisco to Minsk. Check out my <a href='/speaking'>speaking page</a> for more.
          %li
            %h3 Functional Reactive Programming on iOS
            %img{:src => '/img/portfolio/frp.jpg'}/
            %div
              %p I self-published <a href='http://leanpub.com/iosfrp/'><em>Functional Reactive Programming on iOS</em></a> in 2013 to detail the benefits of functional problem-solving approaches to everyday iOS programming challenges. The book breaks down large, complex theories into small, understandable chunks.
          %li
            %h3 UICollectionView: The Complete Guide
            %img{:src => '/img/portfolio/collectionviews.png'}/
            .content
              %p <a href='http://www.amazon.com/gp/product/B00IHZKDCU/ref=as_li_tl?ie=UTF8&camp=1789&creative=390957&creativeASIN=B00IHZKDCU&linkCode=as2&tag=ashfur-20&linkId=O4P4HCCUTMDXYEBT'><em>UICollectionView: The Complete Guide</em></a>, was published in 2013 by Addison-Wesley, and a second edition published the following year. It covers every aspect of using UICollectionView, including many thorough code examples.
          %li
            %h3 Your First Swift App
            %img{:src => '/img/portfolio/yourfirstswiftapp.png'}/
            .content
              %p <a href='http://leanpub.com/yourfirstswiftapp'><em>Your First Swift App</em></a> introduces readers to iOS: helping them with their first Xcode project to submitting to the App Store. The book is intended for people with some development experience, but no experience writing iOS apps.

